deleteTrack(25.10)                                          deleteTrack(25.10)

Name
       deleteTrack - Deletes a set of tracks in the database

Syntax
       deleteTrack

       [-help]

       [-dir {<X|Y>}]

       [-layer <layerNameList>]

       Deletes  a set of tracks in the database. Without arguments, it deletes
       all the tracks in the database.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each deleteTrack parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man deleteTrack.

       -dir {<X | Y>}
              Specifies  the direction of the track to be deleted. X indicates
              vertical lines; Y indicates horizontal lines. This is optional.

       -layer <layerNameList>
              Specifies the routing layer on which the tracks to  be  deleted.
              You can specify more than one layer. This is optional.

Examples
              * The following command deletes the track between M1 and M2:

                deleteTrack -layer {M1 M2}

              * The following command deletes the vertical tracks:

                deleteTrack -dir X

